Name: 6x2 Elite Restriction Release_a04 (Pub)
Description:
EnemiesNoSync Edition, For Pubbing. Breaking the Limit in 6x2. What is Elite Restriction Release? 90% of enemies have a chance to spawn in Elite variant, Elite enemies stats are tuned significantly, for Balance. New Elite variants are also borns with new quirks to ensure the enjoyment of the difficulty.
    Alpha 04: 
  - Removed SuperElite Bulk, Elite Glyphid Spawn out from the difficulty, renamed SuperElite tag back into Elite, some enemies have been renamed to be shorter.
  - Reworked entire structure of the Elite promotion (for normal enemies, excluding custom stationaries) to be more fair:
    + DuringEncounters, no longer promotes Elite enemies, instead they are promoted during a Swarm or Pressure/Normal Wave.
    + 4 maximum Elite enemies are allowed per Common Enemies and Special pool spawn, 3 for Disruptives Enemies. Once all Elite enemies from the corresponding EnemyPool type dies, a cooldown of 15, 25, 35s will be initiated for Common, Special and Disruptive enemy pool respectively before they can be promoted into Elites again.
    + Due to the Elite count being capped significantly (along with added Cooldown) compare to last time, Promotion chance for all Elites are slightly raised up.
  - Stationary Elite enemies: Removed temperature burst requirement increase. Specific changes are below:
    + Elite Cave Leech: Grab Speed and Damage x2.5 -> x2. Has the heath of a Guard -> a Tri-Jaw (use Common Health scaling instead of Elite).
    + Elite Spitballer: Has the health of a Spitballer -> Has the health of a Sentinel (use Large Health scaling instead of Elite).
    + Elite Barrager: Has the health of a Breeder -> Barrager (use Large Health scaling instead of Elite). Damage Dealt +12.5%.
    + Elite Breeder: It gets a different treatment here. Only 1 Elite Breeder exists in the map, and can spawn only ONCE. Also Removed temperature burst requirement increase. Has the health of a Nexus -> Breeder (use Large Scaling instead of Elite Scaling).
  - Revert all previous Elite variants's temperature burst changes, now apply new change formula:
    + Swarmer: Increase Burning requirement and Warming/Cooling Rate by x10 times (100 burn temp). It will die after being Burned but not Frozen.
    + Grunt variants, Web Spitter Acid Spitter, Septic Spreader, Menace and Trawler: Increase temp requirement and warming rate by x2 times.
    + Mactera Spawn, Trijaw, Brundle and Grabber: Increase temp requirement by x2 times. Brundle and Grabber Freezing temp remains the same.
    + Praetorian, Stingtail, Warden, Youngling, Shellback and Bomber variants: Increase temp requirement and warming rate by x1.5 times. Bomber variants Freezing temp remain the same.
    + Remaining enemies: No change in temperature. 
    + Exploder: Unable to be Ignited or Frozen.
  - Additionally, some Elite enemies are adjusted:
    + Elite Warden: No longer spawns Elite slasher upon being Alerted. Reduce MaxBuffedTarget by 2 (17 -> 15).
    + Elite Shellback: Now has +400% movement speed (not when rolling), so it can reposition itself significantly quicker and do more spit attacks.
    + Elite Fire Bomber: Has the heath of an Oppressor -> a Barrage Infector (Buff). No longer stuns and fear immune.
  - Because Elite enemies are no longer promoting DuringEncounters, 2 WaveSpawners will be added to spawn some enemies. Details are below:
    + Common WS: Difficulty 10 every 45s (Delay by 15s at the start of mission). Spawn Grunts that can be Promoted and Elited. 
    + Special WS: Difficulty 20 every 70s (Delay by 15s at the start of mission). Spawn Swarmer/Web Spitter/Exploder/Mactera Spawn (cannot be Veteran'd to other types) with 30%/30%/20%/20% weight ratio. All of these enemies can be Elited.
  - Revert Dotty's resistance buff back to previous 75% value.
